title: Led Zeppelin - 1980.06.24 Hannover, Germany
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1980.06.24 Hannover, Germany   

Artist: Led Zeppelin
Date: 1980-06-24
Location: Hanover, Germany
Venue: Messehalle
Source: Soundboard (audience patch on Trampled Underfoot)

Source: 
Soundboard (1st gen cassette) Incomplete excellent soundboard 
recording. The recording is a very good balanced professional 
board tape.

Audience (3rd Gen Cassette) Incomplete very good audience 
recording.

Tracklist:

LZ 1980-06-24 D1T01 - Train Kept a Rollin
LZ 1980-06-24 D1T02 - Nobodys Fault but Mine
LZ 1980-06-24 D1T03 - Black Dog
LZ 1980-06-24 D1T04 - In The Evening
LZ 1980-06-24 D1T05 - Rain Song
LZ 1980-06-24 D1T06 - Hot Dog
LZ 1980-06-24 D1T07 - All of My Love
LZ 1980-06-24 D1T08 - Trampled Underfoot
LZ 1980-06-24 D1T09 - Since Ive Been Loving You
LZ 1980-06-24 D1T10 - Achilles Last Stand
LZ 1980-06-24 D2T01 - White Summer
LZ 1980-06-24 D2T02 - Black Mountainside
LZ 1980-06-24 D2T03 - Kashmir
LZ 1980-06-24 D2T04 - Stairway To Heaven
LZ 1980-06-24 D2T05 - Rock and Roll
LZ 1980-06-24 D2T06 - Communication Breakdown

Notes:
Complete show minus some audience cheering between Stairway To 
Heaven/Rock And Roll. Audience recording used to splice in 
missing section during Trampled Underfoot.

Comments: 
The concert is quite low key and relaxed. Plant mocks the audience 
for their passivity (even saying, off-mike, "Hannover, fucking 
horrible place!" before In The Evening). He even tries to get Bonham 
to play Moby Dick to liven the audience ("No way, mate. No way." Bonzo 
says to Plant). Highlights include All My Love with Jones playing the 
keyboard solo in at the correct tempo (he often plays it too fast on 
this tour). They rhythm section leaves Page unaccompanied at one point 
during the Trampled Underfoot solo sounding very interesting. Since 
I've Been Loving You is one of the best versions from this tour
